{
  "bookId": "laozi-boshu",
  "num": 45,
  "title": "第四十五章（請靚）",
  "author": "老子",
  "authorId": "Laozi",
  "dynasty": "周",
  "era": "周",
  "genre": "prose",
  "verses": [
    {
      "text": "大成若缺 其用不敝 大盈若盅　其用不窮 大直如屈 大巧如拙 大贏如絀"
    },
    {
      "text": "躁勝寒　靜勝炅 清靜可以為天下正"
    }
  ],
  "sections": {},
  "annotations": [],
  "layers": {
    "heshanggong": [
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 34
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "其用心如是，則無弊盡時也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 34
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "謂道德大盈滿之君也。若沖者，貴不敢驕也，富不敢奢也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 15,
          "end": 16
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "其用心如是，則無窮盡時也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-4",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 34
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "大直，謂修道法度正直如一也。若屈者，不與俗人爭，若可屈折。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-5",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 34
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "大巧謂多才術也。若拙者，亦不敢見其能。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-6",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 34
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "大辯者，智無疑。若訥者，口無辟。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-7",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 1
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "勝，極也。春夏陽氣躁疾於上，萬物盛大，極則寒，寒則零落死亡也。言人不當剛躁也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-8",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 16
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "秋冬萬物靜於黃泉之下，極則熱，熱者生之源。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-9",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 16
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "能清靜則為天下之長，持身正則無終已時也。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ],
    "wangbi": [
      {
        "id": "wangbi-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 34
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "隨物而成，不為一象，故若缺也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 34
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "大盈充足，隨物而與，無所愛矜，故若沖也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 34
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "隨物而直，直不在一，故若屈也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-4",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 34
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "大巧，因自然以成器，不造為異端，故若拙也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-5",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 34
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "大辯因物而言，己無所造，故若訥也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-6",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 34
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "躁罷然後勝寒，靜無為以勝熱，以此推之，則清靜為天下正也。靜則全物之真，躁則犯物之性，故惟清靜，乃得如上諸大也。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ]
  },
